The paper deals with succinct data structures for representing deterministic and non-deterministic finite automata, which are primarily studied in the field of formal languages (cs.FL). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in designing optimal space bounds for the data structures. The algorithms and techniques used in the paper are related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) concepts in the form of language acceptance checking.
